ly that one match. The challenge round was used in the early history of tennis (from 1877 through 1921),<ref>{{cite news |title=Abolition of Challenge Rounds|url=https://paperspast.natlib.govt.nz/newspapers/EP19220320.2.111.2?query=Paris%20International%20Championships|via=paperspast.natlib.govt.nz|newspaper=Evening Post |volume=CIII |issue=65 |date=20 March 1922|accessdate=11 December 2016}}</ref> in some tournaments not all. (**) denotes challenge round\n\n==Career finals==\n===Singles (43 titles, 43 runner-ups)===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#eeeeee\"\n|'''Legend (43\u201343)'''\n|- style=\"background:#98fb98;\"\n| Win\n|- style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"\n| Loss\n|}\n\n{| class=\"sortable wikitable\"\n!style=\"width:25px\"|No.\n!style=\"width:45px\"|Result\n!style=\"width:60px\"|Date\n!style=\"width:240px\"|Tournament\n!style=\"width:50px\"|Surface\n!style=\"width:170px\"|Opponent\n!style=\"width:180px\" class=\"unsortable\"|Score\n|-\n| 1.\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Loss\n| May 1888\n| Fitzwilliam Club Championship<ref>{{cite web|title=FITZWILLIAM CLUB CH. Tournament Draw|url=https://app.thetennisbase.com/?enlace=tournament&accion=draw&torneoSearch=FITZWILLIAM%20CLUB%20CH.&year=1888 |publisher=The Tennis Base |date=2016 |accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref>\n| Grass\n| {{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} Tom Campion\n| 9\u20137, 7\u20135, 5\u20137, 6\u20130\n|- \n| 2.\n| style=\"background:#ffa07a;\"|Loss\n| Jun 1889\n| [[Manchester Open|Northern Championships]]\n| Grass\n| {{flagicon|Ireland|1783}} [[Willoughby Hamilton]]\n| 6\u20133, 3\u20136, 6\u20131, 6\u20132\n|-\n| 3.\n| style=\"background:#98fb98;\"|Win\n| Jun 1889\n| [[Dublin University Championships|Dublin University LT Championships]]<ref>{{cite web|title=DUBLIN UNIVERSITY CH. Tournament Draw 1889|url=https://app.thetennisbase.com/?enlace=tournament&accion=draw&torneoSearch=DUBLIN%20UNIVERSITY%20CH.&year=1889 |publisher=The Tennis Base |date=2016 |accessdate=13 December 2016}}</ref>\n| Hard\n| {{fla